        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a fixed quote</a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-trust">
        <div><strong>Same day</strong>Emergency spring &amp; opener repairs</div>
        <div><strong>$700&ndash;$8K</strong>Motor swap to premium install range</div>
        <div><strong>AS 4505</strong>Garage door safety compliant</div>
        <div><strong>5&ndash;10 yr</strong>Door &amp; motor manufacturer warranty</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">What we do</span>
      <h2>Five garage-door services.</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        From an emergency spring replacement before the school run, through to a
        full new insulated sectional with a smart belt-drive motor &mdash; we do
        the assessment, the supply and the install in one trip.
      </p>

      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/garage-door-installation/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9728;</div>
          <h3>Garage door installation</h3>
          <p>New sectional, roller or tilt doors. Single $1.8K&ndash;$3K, double $2.5K&ndash;$5K, premium insulated/timber-look $4K&ndash;$8K. Includes opener, two remotes, on-site testing and app pairing.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See installation &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/garage-door-repair/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9783;</div>
          <h3>Garage door repair</h3>
          <p>Broken torsion or extension springs, snapped cables, bent panels, door off-track, dodgy safety sensors. Most repairs $250&ndash;$900 completed in one visit. Same-day emergency call-out.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See repairs &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/motor-replacement/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9783;</div>
          <h3>Motor replacement</h3>
          <p>Quiet belt-drive upgrades, smart Wi-Fi openers with Google Home/Alexa, battery backup for power outages. Supplied &amp; fitted from $700&ndash;$1,600. Merlin, B&amp;D Smart, Centurion.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See motors &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/sectional-doors/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9618;</div>
          <h3>Sectional doors</h3>
          <p>Insulated steel and timber-look sectional doors. Better insulation, quieter operation, more headroom than rollers. Colorbond colour-match to your roof. B&amp;D, Steel-Line, Dominator stocked.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See sectional doors &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/roller-doors/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9608;</div>
          <h3>Roller doors</h3>
          <p>Colorbond roller doors &mdash; durable, budget-friendly, simple. The classic Australian garage door. Great where ceiling clearance is tight. Centurion Australian-made, B&amp;D Smart Phantom available.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See roller doors &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <figure class="image-banner">
    <img src="/images/result.jpg" alt="Brand-new double garage door fully open" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <figcaption>B&amp;D, Merlin, Steel-Line — same-day on most repairs.</figcaption>
  </figure>


  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why a Casey specialist</span>
      <h2>Three things every Casey garage-door job needs to get right.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; max-width: 60rem;">
        <div>
          <h3>Builder-grade doors are hitting the failure curve.</h3>
          <p>
            The City of Casey has been the fastest-growing council area in
            Victoria for most of the last decade. That means thousands of
            8&ndash;15 year-old homes across Cranbourne East/West/North/Park,
            Berwick, Narre Warren and the newer Hampton Park estates &mdash; all
            running the cheapest spring, roller and opener spec the builder
            could fit. We see the same failures all week: cheap extension
            springs snapping, original chain-drive openers stripping gears,
            bottom panels rusting where they meet the slab. Most owners
            don&rsquo;t realise a 15-cycle-a-day double-door uses up its
            10,000-cycle springs in seven years.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Quiet motors matter when the bedroom is above the garage.</h3>
          <p>
            Modern Casey homes are double-storey on small blocks &mdash; the
            master bedroom, the kids&rsquo; rooms or the home office is almost
            always directly above the garage. A chain-drive opener at 5am
            wakes the whole house. We default to <strong>belt-drive
            motors</strong> (Merlin SilentDrive, B&amp;D Smart Phantom,
            Centurion Reno) on every new install. The price difference is
            small; the lifestyle difference is enormous. Plenty of
            customers ring us to upgrade <em>just</em> the motor because
            the door&rsquo;s fine but the noise is unbearable.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>AS 4505 safety compliance &mdash; not optional.</h3>
          <p>
            AS 4505 is the Australian Standard for garage doors and motorised
            shutters. Every powered door must have a working auto-reverse
            (door reverses when it hits an obstruction), photoelectric safety
            sensors at 150&ndash;200mm above the slab, and a quick-release
            mechanism for manual operation. A surprising number of older
            Cranbourne doors fail at least one of these &mdash; usually the
            safety sensors have been bypassed because they kept tripping in
            sunlight. We test all three on every service visit and replace or
            re-align sensors at no extra charge.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Service areas</span>
